```text id="fabricator-ui-93821"
Build a professional, enterprise-grade, UI-only SaaS web application for a “Fabricator Management Platform”. This is a B2B system used by fabricators, traders, and distributors for managing projects, inventory, pricing, billing, and operations.

Important:
- UI only. No backend, no real APIs, no integrations.
- Use realistic mock data and simulate states.
- The product should feel like a serious SaaS platform with monetization and operational depth.
- Prioritize clarity, scalability, and business usability.
- This is not a simple CRUD app — it should feel like a production SaaS tool.

Design style:
- Clean, modern enterprise SaaS dashboard (similar to ERP/Fintech tools)
- Neutral background, strong typography, subtle borders
- Clear spacing, grid system, and visual hierarchy
- Use restrained color system with semantic colors for states
- Highly readable tables and dense data views
- Professional, not flashy

App structure:
- Left sidebar navigation
- Top header with search, org switcher, notifications, profile, wallet balance
- Main content area with cards, tables, charts, drawers, and modals

Sidebar navigation:
- Dashboard
- Projects
- Inventory
- Pricing Engine
- Billing & Wallet
- Payments
- Supply Chain
- OCR Uploads
- Reports (CA / GST)
- Batch Processing
- Admin Panel
- Settings

-------------------------------------
1) Dashboard (Business Overview)
-------------------------------------
Show a high-level operational + SaaS overview.

Sections:
- KPI cards:
  - Total SFT processed
  - Wallet balance
  - Revenue generated
  - Pending invoices
  - Low stock alerts
  - Active projects
- Usage meter (SFT consumption vs credits)
- Revenue graph (SaaS earnings)
- Inventory alerts panel
- Recent activity timeline
- Pending payments widget
- Supply chain activity snapshot

-------------------------------------
2) Projects (Core Fabrication Flow)
-------------------------------------
Main working area for fabricators.

Include:
- Project list table:
  - Project name
  - Client
  - Total SFT
  - Status
  - Cost estimate
  - Progress
- Project detail screen:
  - Drawings / measurements section
  - BOM (Bill of Materials)
  - Cost breakdown
  - Pricing applied
  - Linked invoices
- BOM section:
  - Profiles
  - Glass
  - Hardware
  - Quantities
- Auto-cost calculation preview (UI only)
- “Process Project” action that shows:
  - SFT usage deduction (mock)
  - Cost estimation

-------------------------------------
3) Inventory Management
-------------------------------------
Critical operational module.

Include:
- Stock overview cards:
  - Profiles
  - Glass
  - Hardware
- Inventory table:
  - Item name
  - Category
  - Quantity
  - Unit
  - Warehouse/location
  - Status (In stock / Low / Out)
- Stock in/out UI:
  - Add stock
  - Remove stock
- Alerts:
  - Low stock warnings
- Multi-level visibility toggle:
  - Fabricator / Distributor / Trader
- BOM auto-deduction preview panel (simulate deduction when project is processed)

-------------------------------------
4) Pricing Engine
-------------------------------------
Flexible pricing configuration UI.

Include:
- Region-based pricing rules
- Customer-type pricing (Retail / Contractor / Bulk)
- Rule builder UI:
  - Conditions (region, material, customer type)
  - Outputs (price per SFT, margin, markup)
- Pricing preview panel:
  - Show calculated price based on rules
- Rule list table with edit/delete

-------------------------------------
5) Billing & Wallet (SaaS Monetization)
-------------------------------------
Core SaaS business module.

Include:
- Wallet balance card
- Credit purchase UI (mock)
- Usage deduction history:
  - SFT used
  - Credits deducted
  - Date/time
- Pricing controls (Admin view):
  - Price per SFT
  - Discount tiers
- Revenue summary:
  - Daily / monthly revenue
- Transaction history table

-------------------------------------
6) Payments (Operational Finance)
-------------------------------------
Track payments and invoices.

Include:
- Invoice table:
  - Invoice ID
  - Client
  - Amount
  - Status (Paid / Pending / Overdue)
  - Due date
- Payment recording modal:
  - Amount
  - Mode
  - Date
- Outstanding summary cards
- Payment timeline per client

-------------------------------------
7) Supply Chain Integration
-------------------------------------
Visualize ecosystem relationships.

Include:
- Network view:
  - Trader → Distributor → Fabricator
- Data visibility controls:
  - What data is shared upstream/downstream
- Linked entities panel:
  - Connected traders/distributors
- Sync status indicators (mock)

-------------------------------------
8) OCR / AI Uploads
-------------------------------------
Smart input module.

Include:
- Upload area:
  - Image / PDF drag-and-drop
- File preview panel
- OCR extraction preview:
  - Measurements
  - Material detection
- AI suggestion panel (mock):
  - Suggested dimensions
  - Detected components
- Validation UI:
  - Highlight errors
  - Allow manual correction

-------------------------------------
9) Reports (CA / GST)
-------------------------------------
Structured financial reports.

Include:
- GST summary cards
- Report filters:
  - Date range
  - Client
  - Project
- Export UI:
  - Excel
  - PDF
- Table preview of reports
- Structured format layout (accounting-friendly)

-------------------------------------
10) Batch Processing
-------------------------------------
Optimization for multiple projects.

Include:
- Project selection table
- Batch processing panel:
  - Combined material usage
  - Cost optimization preview
- Summary:
  - Total SFT
  - Total cost
  - Savings (mock)

-------------------------------------
11) Admin Panel
-------------------------------------
For SaaS owner/operator.

Include:
- Revenue metrics:
  - Total revenue
  - Active users
  - ARPU
- Usage analytics:
  - SFT processed
  - Credit consumption
- Pricing control panel
- System health overview

-------------------------------------
12) Offline Mode (UI Simulation)
-------------------------------------
Include:
- Offline indicator badge
- “Working offline” banner
- Sync queue panel:
  - Pending actions
  - Sync status
- Manual sync button

-------------------------------------
13) Multi-language Support (UI only)
-------------------------------------
Include:
- Language switcher (English / Telugu / Hindi)
- UI should demonstrate:
  - Text switching (mock)
  - Icon-supported navigation

-------------------------------------
Key UI behaviors:
- Clear state indicators everywhere:
  - Active / Completed / Pending / Error
- Use badges, chips, and labels consistently
- Tables must support:
  - Sorting
  - Filtering
  - Search
- Use modals and side drawers for actions (edit, add, process)
- Use stepper or workflow indicators where needed

-------------------------------------
Data (mock structure examples):
-------------------------------------
Projects:
- id, name, client, sft, status, cost, created_at

Inventory:
- id, item_name, category, quantity, unit, location, status

Wallet:
- balance, credits_used, credits_added, transactions

Invoices:
- id, client, amount, status, due_date, paid_date

Pricing rules:
- id, region, customer_type, material, price_per_sft

OCR files:
- id, file_url, extracted_data, validation_status

-------------------------------------
Technical preferences:
- React-style component architecture
- Reusable UI components
- Mock JSON data
- No backend logic
- Focus on layout, UX, and system clarity

-------------------------------------
Final goal:
-------------------------------------
A polished, scalable, SaaS-grade UI that clearly represents:
- Monetization (wallet + SFT billing)
- Operations (projects + inventory)
- Intelligence (OCR + pricing)
- Finance (payments + reports)
- Ecosystem (supply chain)

The UI should feel like a real product that could be shipped after backend integration.
```
